    <mxCell id="fact1" value="&lt;b&gt;Why a key pair?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font style='font-size:10px'&gt;Only the private key can create a signature that the public key can verify. If you don't hold the private key, you cannot forge a valid DKIM signature for that domain.&lt;/font&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fffbea;strokeColor=#e67e22;fontSize=11;align=left;spacingLeft=8;verticalAlign=top;spacingTop=6;" vertex="1" parent="1">
