    <mxCell id="fact2" value="&lt;b&gt;Why does it survive forwarding?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font style='font-size:10px'&gt;DKIM is tied to the message content, not the sending IP. Forwarding servers pass the signature along untouched, so the recipient can still verify it — unlike SPF which checks the sending IP.&lt;/font&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#e8f8ee;strokeColor=#27ae60;fontSize=11;align=left;spacingLeft=8;verticalAlign=top;spacingTop=6;" vertex="1" parent="1">
