    <mxCell id="fact3" value="&lt;b&gt;What DKIM does NOT do&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font style='font-size:10px'&gt;DKIM does not validate the visible From: header on its own. An attacker could sign a message with their own domain's private key while spoofing your From: header. DMARC alignment closes that gap.&lt;/font&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fff0f0;strokeColor=#c0392b;fontSize=11;align=left;spacingLeft=8;verticalAlign=top;spacingTop=6;" vertex="1" parent="1">
